social_posts.post_text:
“You must determine where you are going in your life, because you cannot get there unless you move in that direction. Random wandering will not move you forward. It will instead disappoint and frustrate you and make you anxious and unhappy and hard to get along with (and then resentful, and then vengeful, and then worse).”⁣
⁣
Meeting @jordan.b.peterson last night was definitely a highlight of this month.⁣
⁣
I remember how in 2020 my friends showed me his video where he shared his thoughts about certain things. I was immediately drawn to this man. I thought to myself: “God, finally someone speaks his truth out there! Finally someone speaks my language!”⁣
⁣
Then I found out that we were born the same day (June 12th)😳. I was like: “Well that explains a lot!” ⁣
⁣
Yesterday I told him that and we laughed about it.⁣
⁣
If you’ll ask me: “Who do I want to become in 5 years?” I’ll answer: “I want to be a female version of everything that this man embodies.”⁣
⁣
Being authentic, standing for what you know is right, being powerful, encouraging and inspiring. We need leaders like this more than ever!❤️⁣
⁣
Aim up! Speak carefully!!!

I truly agree with Winston’t Churchill words: “If you find a job you love, you’ll never work again...”

18 years ago I found modeling… or I should say it found me…

I’ll never forget the conversation I had with one model from my agency when I was 18 y.o. She came home one day after the shoot and was complaining about it. Saying that she hates modeling.

We spoke and I’ll never forget her words: “Well the difference between you and me, Polina, is that you love it!”

She was right - I did! I still do!!!

And even tho in a past 4 years I’ve been focusing more on the aspects of managing other careers, and coaching women, I still enjoy shooting here and there.❤️

Every shoot allows me to express myself differently. It allows to show to the world a different side of me. Sometimes finding sides of myself that I didn’t even know existed. 

It’s all about self-expression. 😉

I was 16 y.o. when I read “The Alchemist” for the first time.
As many of you know it’s a story about a shepherd boy named Santiago who travels from his homeland in Spain to the Egyptian desert in search of a treasure. 

There’s a quote in that book, that stuck with me. It says: “When you want something, all the universe conspires in helping you to achieve it.

This book is about a hero’s journey. 
I think we are all heroes of our own journeys.

This one is mine. 
It’s not an easy one, but it’s raw and authentic.

From a little Ukrainian girl who was born in Kherson I traveled around the world in search of my own treasure.

I don’t know where this journey leads me, but what I know is that I already found many treasures. My treasures come in a form of people. They share with me their stories. I share mine. 

This time I was invited to share my story with the people of Google.❤️
It was my first time becoming a public speaker. After 90 mins of me talking, I thought my heart would explode with amount of love I had for those people. People I’ve never met, people I didn’t know, but people whose life matters to me. 

After the talk I got a lot of an amazing feedback, but the most important was this one: “I feel like her session has caused the most discussion and sparked the most interest from the sessions done by this group.”

And that’s exactly what I wanted. I wanted to shake them to their core, I wanted to provoke people to think, to talk, to share. I wanted to shred everything that isn’t helping their greatness. 

What I found in my journey as a coach - that it’s not about being liked. I honestly stopped caring if people like me or not. What I care about is that their life works. 

I think real love doesn’t always come in a nice and sweet package - it comes in a raw and authentic package. It comes as a stand.
It’s like a parent’s love - they want your life to work and they’ll do everything in their power to help you to achieve everything you want!

With love, 
as always,
Polina
You can enjoy this world and other people in it when you don’t need them to complete your identity.

And the simplest of all truths was revealed: everything is always good and fair. Who follows himself does not wander. 
Who loses himself finds the world…
Who finds the world finds himself…

Your journey always leads you back to you.

I know sometimes life gets hard. Really really hard!
And if you’re going through a rough time, the hardest part is to keep alive an empowering context of everything that is going on around you.

Trust me, I’ve been there! Many-many times!!!

4 years ago I found myself on the bottom of my personal “evolutionary ocean”. I literally felt that my identity was crashed!
Little did I know - that too was a good thing!
Back then I had two options: a) be sucked into the victimhood, chose to blame (and I had all the reasons to), 
b) remind myself that the only person who is in charge of saying how my life is going to go is ME! Roll up my sleeves, reconnect to the vision of what I want and work daily on drawing myself closer to that vision.

4 years later I woke up with the feeling that I collapsed time. The woman that looks at me in the mirror is the woman I saw in my vision 4 years ago.
She closed the chapter of her first marriage with nothing but love and gratitude for her ex husband. I mean it! He’s great.

It wasn’t an easy ride. But it was definitely worth it. 
I wouldn’t be who I am today if it wasn’t for all the pain that I’ve experienced in the past. That pain got me present and got me back on the path to ME.

So if you are in the bottom today - know - this isn’t the end!!! 4 years later you might wake up in a beautiful house, you might feel the happiest you’ve ever been, you might have an incredible people around you… you might be in a gitty disbelieve that you get to be YOU!!!❤️ 

Keep going! It’s all worth it! Just trust me on that!

Oops… I did it again🪂

Fear doesn’t exist anywhere except in the mind. 

And one of the greatest discoveries is to find out that you can do what you once was afraid you couldn’t do.
I wanted to see if I’ll be afraid this time… but no, I wasn’t. 

I was very calm but at the same time excited to push my limits and do the highest jump I’ve ever done.💪 18,000 ft.

After working with women I realized that, there’re 6 points of support that every woman needs:

1. a strong personality 
2. an energetic body
3. a professional mastery
4. spirituality 
5. happy relationship
6. supportive community of friends

When the woman has all these components, no matter what difficulties she’ll be facing, she’ll feel safe.
If the woman is constantly feels unsafe, she’ll be living on hormones of stress and would get tired and fade like a flower that doesn’t get the sun.☀️

I can’t stress enough how important it is to develop, nurture and maintain each of those 6 components if you want to live a happy and fulfilled life❤️

Продолжается набор на ДВАДЦАТЬ ПЕРВЫЙ марафон-легкости! 👇

Марафон, как стиль жизни. Марафон, который когда-то изменил мою жизнь, а теперь продолжает трансформировать жизни женщин. 

✅ Старт - 30 октября❗️

✅ Марафон, который освободит тебя от всего того, что по-прежнему сковывает твою жизнь.

✅ Научиться генерировать энергию везде и всегда.

✅ Я могу долго рассказывать о чем марафон, но лучше просто почитайте отзывы предыдущих участниц. Ими все сказано😉

✅ Замечу, что каждая приходит ко мне с разными целями - и не для всех это «похудеть». Для кого-то это нехватка сил и энергии, заниженная самооценка или проблемы в семье. Но то, что КАЖДАЯ получит, то за чем пришла - я гарантирую!
Я научу всех и каждую влюбиться в себя и в свою жизнь раз и навсегда!!! 

✅  Я расскажу вам АБСОЛЮТНО ВСЕ свои секреты по поддержанию энергии (ооо девочки знают, что энергии в марафоне хоть отбавляй - оживет даже мертвый😂), также вам будет предоставлено по-шаговое каждодневное расписание. Меню, расписание и видео тренировок дома и в зале, дыхательные упражнения, упражнения для лица, осанки, упражнения на самооценку, упражнения для подсознания, а также бонусом я научу вас двум уникальным медитациям, которые помогли мне реализовать ооочень многие цели в жизни!!! И еще много и много других крутых трюков. .

✅ Марафон я буду проходить вместе с вами, поэтому у Вас будет каждодневная поддержка от меня и от всех участниц. (отзывы предыдущих участниц вы можете прочитать в картинках). . или на @boydmethod

Happy New Year my dear friends!🎄✨

Life doesn’t get easier, but it definitely gets more interesting! 
Never stop believing.❤️ Because often it’s all you’ve got… and often it’s more than enough! 

I hope this year will prove you that magic exists.✨

I have thousands of photos from London, I guess it’s time I share a few.😉

Even tho it was my first time in UK, after 2 weeks of endless castle visits I feel like I can easily lead a guided tours in this country.🤣 

The weather overall was sh*t, but it didn’t prevent us from having so much fun! I should say - a hell of a time!😂 

This trip to London will forever stay in my heart as one of the most beautiful trips I’ve ever taken. I love beauty, I love class, I love things that last - and London was all that. 

Every corner has so much history behind it, that you inevitably feel as a time traveler. Something I so deeply miss in America.

Now I really want to come back to London during the summer - to see that the weather can actually be nice. 

Thank London - you made these Christmas holidays magical.✨🎄
